r559 | darwin | 2009-02-09 19:37:54 +0800 (Mon, 09 Feb 2009) | 9 lines

* Subclass asyncore.file_dispatcher and override __init__ method so that file
  descriptor wouldn't be set to non-blocking. Setting MPlayer's stdout seems
  to make MPlayer hang. I haven't been able to fully reproduce the problem
  since it seems to occur randomly.
* Since the fd's are now blocking again, select.select is now used to check if
  data can actually be read.
* Buffering causes problems with select.select, set Popen.bufsize=0
* MPlayer.query() now uses _file.readline() internally

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r558 | darwin | 2009-02-09 19:29:57 +0800 (Mon, 09 Feb 2009) | 2 lines

Prepend 'pausing_keep' to all commands to preserve MPlayer's pause state

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r557 | darwin | 2009-02-09 17:57:07 +0800 (Mon, 09 Feb 2009) | 3 lines

Renamed _file.callback() -> _file.publish() to reflect similarity with the
publish/subscribe design pattern

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r556 | darwin | 2009-02-09 14:18:31 +0800 (Mon, 09 Feb 2009) | 4 lines

* Change terms: handlers -> subscribers (patterned after Observer design pattern)
* add_handler(handler_cb) -> attach(subscriber_cb)
* remove_handler(handler_id) -> detach(subscriber_cb)

------------------------------------------------------------------------
